expPortTable.name: expPortTable
expPortTable.description: A list of expansion port entries.

expPortEntry.name: expPortEntry
expPortEntry.description: An expansion port entry for a single port

expPort_module_id.name: expPort_module_id
expPort_module_id.description: The module ID of the sensor module installed. Blank string indicates that no module is installed.

expPort_module_type.name: expPort_module_type
expPort_module_type.description: The type of sensor module installed. NONE=no module, AMP=AmpDetect module, TEMP=temperature sensor, DRY=dry contact sensor.

expPort_label.name: expPort_label
expPort_label.description: The label for the expansion port. Ports default to the label 'Extn', for port n.

expPort_amps.name: expPort_amps
expPort_amps.description: The reading of the amperage probe, in milliamps.

expPort_total_amp_seconds.name: expPort_total_amp_seconds
expPort_total_amp_seconds.description: The accumulated total of amp-seconds on the AmpDetect.

expPort_total_amp_seconds_since_time.name: expPort_total_amp_seconds_since_time
expPort_total_amp_seconds_since_time.description: The UTC time (seconds since 1/1/1970) of the beginning of the accumulated total of amp-seconds on the AmpDetect. Writing a value to this attribute resets the accumulated total amp-seconds and sets this time to the current time.

expPort_amps_enabled.name: expPort_amps_enabled
expPort_amps_enabled.description: Amperage probe alarm enabled(1) or disabled(0).

expPort_amps_min.name: expPort_amps_min
expPort_amps_min.description: The amperage probe minimum, from 0 to 30000 milliamps.

expPort_amps_max.name: expPort_amps_max
expPort_amps_max.description: The amperage probe maximum, from 0 to 30000 milliamps.

expPort_amps_uV_per_10mA.name: expPort_amps_uV_per_10mA
expPort_amps_uV_per_10mA.description: The scaling factor used for the amperage probe to convert microvolts measured from the Amp Detect into 10s of milliamps of current. Needs to be set based on the type of Amp Detect module installed.

expPort_amps_max_range.name: expPort_amps_max_range
expPort_amps_max_range.description: The maximum RMS milliamps measureable by the AmpDetect.

expPort_ext_temp.name: expPort_ext_temp
expPort_ext_temp.description: The reading of the external temperature probe, in degrees F or degrees C (depends on netBotz-ismetric).

expPort_ext_temp_enabled.name: expPort_ext_temp_enabled
expPort_ext_temp_enabled.description: External temperature probe alarm enabled(1) or disabled(0).

expPort_ext_temp_min.name: expPort_ext_temp_min
expPort_ext_temp_min.description: The external temperature probe minimum, in degrees F or degrees C (depends on netBotz-ismetric).

expPort_ext_temp_max.name: expPort_ext_temp_max
expPort_ext_temp_max.description: The external temperature probe maximum, in degrees F or degrees C (depends on netBotz-ismetric).

expPort_ext_temp_uV_per_degreeC.name: expPort_ext_temp_uV_per_degreeC
expPort_ext_temp_uV_per_degreeC.description: The scaling factor used for the external temperature probe to convert microvolts measured from the temperature sensor into degrees C. Needs to be set based on the type of temperature sensor module installed.

expPort_ext_temp_uV_at_0_degreeC.name: expPort_ext_temp_uV_at_0_degreeC
expPort_ext_temp_uV_at_0_degreeC.description: The offset used for the external temperature probe of microvolts measured from the temperature sensor at zero degrees C. Needs to be set based on the type of temperature sensor module installed.

expPort_ext_temp_min_range.name: expPort_ext_temp_min_range
expPort_ext_temp_min_range.description: The minimum temperature measureable by the temperature sensor, in tenths of a degree C. Needs to be set based on the type of temperature sensor module installed.

expPort_ext_temp_max_range.name: expPort_ext_temp_max_range
expPort_ext_temp_max_range.description: The maximum temperature measureable by the temperature sensor, in tenths of a degree C. Needs to be set based on the type of temperature sensor module installed.

expPort_ext_dry.name: expPort_ext_dry
expPort_ext_dry.description: The current value of the external dry contact sensor: 0=Open, 1=Closed, -1=N/A

expPort_ext_dry_alarm_value.name: expPort_ext_dry_alarm_value
expPort_ext_dry_alarm_value.description: The value to generate alarms on for the external dry contact sensor: 0=Open, 1=Closed

expPort_ext_dry_enabled.name: expPort_ext_dry_enabled
expPort_ext_dry_enabled.description: External dry contact sensor alarm enabled(1) or disabled(0).

expPort_ext_dry_label.name: expPort_ext_dry_label
expPort_ext_dry_label.description: The sensor name/label for the dry contact sensor

expPort_ext_dry_open_label.name: expPort_ext_dry_open_label
expPort_ext_dry_open_label.description: The sensor name/label for the open(0) state for the dry contact sensor

expPort_ext_dry_closed_label.name: expPort_ext_dry_closed_label
expPort_ext_dry_closed_label.description: The sensor name/label for the closed(0) state for the dry contact sensor

expPort_ext_dry_open_to_close_millis.name: expPort_ext_dry_open_to_close_millis
expPort_ext_dry_open_to_close_millis.description: The minimum number of milliseconds that the dry contact sensor must read closed before the state is changed from open to closed.

expPort_ext_dry_close_to_open_millis.name: expPort_ext_dry_close_to_open_millis
expPort_ext_dry_close_to_open_millis.description: The minimum number of milliseconds that the dry contact sensor must read openbefore the state is changed from closed to open.

expPort_ext_dry_response.name: expPort_ext_dry_response
expPort_ext_dry_response.description: The type of alert response for the dry contact sensor: ALERT=e-mail with no pictures, CAMERA=e-mail with pictures from camera.

expPort_ext_humi.name: expPort_ext_humi
expPort_ext_humi.description: The reading of the external humidity probe, in percent.

expPort_ext_humi_enabled.name: expPort_ext_humi_enabled
expPort_ext_humi_enabled.description: External humidity probe alarm enabled(1) or disabled(0).

expPort_ext_humi_min.name: expPort_ext_humi_min
expPort_ext_humi_min.description: The external humidity probe minimum, in percent.

expPort_ext_humi_max.name: expPort_ext_humi_max
expPort_ext_humi_max.description: The external humidity probe maximum, in percent.

expPort_ext_humi_uV_per_percent.name: expPort_ext_humi_uV_per_percent
expPort_ext_humi_uV_per_percent.description: The scaling factor used for the external humidity probe to convert microvolts measured from the humidity sensor into percent. Needs to be set based on the type of humidity sensor module installed.

expPort_ext_humi_uV_at_0_percent.name: expPort_ext_humi_uV_at_0_percent
expPort_ext_humi_uV_at_0_percent.description: The offset used for the external humidity probe of microvolts measured from the humidity sensor at zero percent. Needs to be set based on the type of humidity sensor module installed.

expPort_ext_humi_min_range.name: expPort_ext_humi_min_range
expPort_ext_humi_min_range.description: The minimum humidity measureable by the humidity sensor, in percent. Needs to be set based on the type of humidity sensor module installed.

expPort_ext_humi_max_range.name: expPort_ext_humi_max_range
expPort_ext_humi_max_range.description: The maximum humidity measureable by the humidity sensor, in percent. Needs to be set based on the type of humidity sensor module installed.

netBotz_prd_crl_mib2_ping.name: netBotz_prd_crl_mib2_ping
netBotz_prd_crl_mib2_ping.description: NetBotz device ping. This object indicates the status of a ping on a device monitored by a NetBotz device.

netBotz_prd_crl_mib2_uptime.name: netBotz_prd_crl_mib2_uptime
netBotz_prd_crl_mib2_uptime.description: The uptime of a device monitored by a NetBotz device.

netBotz_prd_crl_mib2_snmpstatus.name: netBotz_prd_crl_mib2_snmpstatus
netBotz_prd_crl_mib2_snmpstatus.description: The SNMP status of a device monitored by a NetBotz device.

netBotz_prd_crl_mib2if_opstatus.name: netBotz_prd_crl_mib2if_opstatus
netBotz_prd_crl_mib2if_opstatus.description: The operational status of a device monitored by a NetBotz device.

netBotz_prd_crl_trap_index.name: netBotz_prd_crl_trap_index
netBotz_prd_crl_trap_index.description: The ID of the crawler which sent the last trap.

netBotz_prd_crl_trap_address.name: netBotz_prd_crl_trap_address
netBotz_prd_crl_trap_address.description: The IP address of the last trap.

netBotz_prd_crl_trap_oid.name: netBotz_prd_crl_trap_oid
netBotz_prd_crl_trap_oid.description: The object id of the attribute on the target device which is the concern of the last trap.

netBotz_prd_crl_trap_botoid.name: netBotz_prd_crl_trap_botoid
netBotz_prd_crl_trap_botoid.description: The object id of the attribute on the NetBotz device which is the concern of the last trap.

netBotz_prd_crl_trap_value.name: netBotz_prd_crl_trap_value
netBotz_prd_crl_trap_value.description: The value of the attribute associated with the last trap.

netBotz_prd_crl_trap_date.name: netBotz_prd_crl_trap_date
netBotz_prd_crl_trap_date.description: The date and time of a specific trap. This field contains the number of seconds elapsed since midnight (00:00:00), January 1, 1970

netBotz_prd_crl_trap_attrib.name: netBotz_prd_crl_trap_attrib
netBotz_prd_crl_trap_attrib.description: The identification number of the attribute in error

netBotz_prd_crl_trap_desc.name: netBotz_prd_crl_trap_desc
netBotz_prd_crl_trap_desc.description: Description or name of the attribute in error

netBotz_prd_crl_ping_offline_trap.name: netBotz_prd_crl_ping_offline_trap
netBotz_prd_crl_ping_offline_trap.description: NetBotz Ping Trap. This trap indicates that replies to a set of pings were not received from a monitored IP address.

netBotz_prd_crl_ping_online_trap.name: netBotz_prd_crl_ping_online_trap
netBotz_prd_crl_ping_online_trap.description: NetBotz Ping Trap. This trap indicates that replies to a set of pings were received from a monitored IP address after a period when no replies had been received.

netBotz_prd_crl_snmp_offline_trap.name: netBotz_prd_crl_snmp_offline_trap
netBotz_prd_crl_snmp_offline_trap.description: NetBotz SNMP Offline Trap. This trap indicates that an SNMP request was not possible on an IP address.

netBotz_prd_crl_snmp_online_trap.name: netBotz_prd_crl_snmp_online_trap
netBotz_prd_crl_snmp_online_trap.description: NetBotz SNMP Online Trap. This trap indicates that an SNMP request succeeded on an IP address where it had previously failed.

netBotz_prd_crl_uptime_online_trap.name: netBotz_prd_crl_uptime_online_trap
netBotz_prd_crl_uptime_online_trap.description: NetBotz Uptime Trap. This trap indicates that a device restart has been detected due to the uptime of the device being reported as less than the previously reported reading.

netBotz_prd_crl_opstatus_offline_trap.name: netBotz_prd_crl_opstatus_offline_trap
netBotz_prd_crl_opstatus_offline_trap.description: NetBotz Interface Offline Trap. This trap indicates that an interface on a device did not respond to an SNMP query on the ifAdminStatus or ifOperStatus objects.

netBotz_prd_crl_opstatus_mismatch_trap.name: netBotz_prd_crl_opstatus_mismatch_trap
netBotz_prd_crl_opstatus_mismatch_trap.description: NetBotz Interface Status Mismatch Trap. This trap indicates that the operational status of a device interface does not match the administrative status.

netBotz_prd_crl_opstatus_match_trap.name: netBotz_prd_crl_opstatus_match_trap
netBotz_prd_crl_opstatus_match_trap.description: NetBotz Interface Status Match Trap. This trap indicates that the operational status of a device interface now matches the administrative status. This trap indicates a transition from a state in which the administrative and operational status did not match.

netBotz_snmp_traptarget.name: netBotz_snmp_traptarget
netBotz_snmp_traptarget.description: Target of traps from the NetBotz device. This field contains the IP address where NetBotz traps are to be sent.

netBotz_snmp_community.name: netBotz_snmp_community
netBotz_snmp_community.description: The read/write community of the NetBotz device.

netBotz_userid_1.name: netBotz_userid_1
netBotz_userid_1.description: The userID of the supervisor account (write-only).

netBotz_password_1.name: netBotz_password_1
netBotz_password_1.description: The password of the supervisor account (write-only).

netBotz_userid_2.name: netBotz_userid_2
netBotz_userid_2.description: The userID of the full read access account (write-only).

netBotz_password_2.name: netBotz_password_2
netBotz_password_2.description: The password of the full read access account (write-only).

netBotz_userid_3.name: netBotz_userid_3
netBotz_userid_3.description: The userID of the minimum read access account (write-only).

netBotz_password_3.name: netBotz_password_3
netBotz_password_3.description: The password of the minimum read access account (write-only).

netBotz_snmp_traptarget2.name: netBotz_snmp_traptarget2
netBotz_snmp_traptarget2.description: Second target of traps from the NetBotz device. This field contains an additional IP address where NetBotz traps are to be sent.

netBotz_snmp_read_community.name: netBotz_snmp_read_community
netBotz_snmp_read_community.description: The read-only community of the NetBotz device.

device_crawlers_trap_index.name: device_crawlers_trap_index
device_crawlers_trap_index.reference: NetBotz Device Crawlers Last Trap ID
device_crawlers_trap_index.description: The ID of the device crawler which sent the last trap.

device_crawlers_trap_address.name: device_crawlers_trap_address
device_crawlers_trap_address.reference: NetBotz Device Crawlers Last Trap Address
device_crawlers_trap_address.description: The IP address of the appliance actually creating the last trap.

device_crawlers_trap_oid.name: device_crawlers_trap_oid
device_crawlers_trap_oid.reference: NetBotz Device Crawlers Target Trap Attribute OID
device_crawlers_trap_oid.description: The object id of the attribute on the device crawlers target device which is the concern of the last trap. The second to last element indicates the index of the source of the problem (1=ICMP Ping, 2=SNMP Agent Status, 256-10239=Network Interfaces 1-9984, 10240 and above, indicates Advanced crawlers data). The last element is the decimal representation of the IP address of the source of the problem.

device_crawlers_trap_botoid.name: device_crawlers_trap_botoid
